e in urban America during World War II. He argues that Mexican American and African American youths, along with many nisei and white youths, used popular culture to oppose accepted modes of youthful behavior, the dominance of white middle-class norms, and expectations from within their own communities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFashionzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aMinority youthzUnited StatesxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aPopular culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSleepy Lagoon Trial, Los Angeles, Calif., 1942-1943. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aYouthzUnited StatesxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aZoot Suit Riots, Los Angeles, Calif., 1943. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a1940s.  aacademic.  aafrican american.  aamerican culture.  aamerican history.  acultural history.  aculture.  aexperimental.  aexperimentation.  agender studies.  ainterviews.  ajazz music.  ajazz musician.  ajitterbug.  alindy hop.  amexican american.  amiddle class.  aminority groups.  aphenomenon.  apolitical.  apolitics.  apopular culture.  arace issues.  arace.  aracism.  aregional.  ascholarly.  asexuality.  aswing music.  aunited states history.  aurban america.  aurban.  aus history.  awartime.  aworld war 2.  awwii.  ayouth culture.  azoot suit.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025301840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093421440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520934214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520934214/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_F